Drawing II expands upon drawing fundamentals and leads the student into a facility with materials and methods, and into finished drawing as an objective.&#8232;&#8232;

Students commented that they enjoyed this course and learned a lot from it. One said that this course “challenged [them] to think about the way [they] draw or create art more carefully.”&#8232;&#8232;

Students who took this course said that Professor Curran was a great instructor and really encouraged and motivated her students. One student commented that Professor Curran “cares about her students and takes the time to get to know her students’ personalities as well as style.” Another student did mention that Professor Curran “had the tendency to unintentionally finish people’s thoughts and take over the conversation again.”&#8232;&#8232;

This course has FNAR 123/523 as its prerequisite.
